text:
I have been eating ee mian more often this week.
The zi char stall at Chin Bee F&B at Blk 143 Teck Whye Lane sells one of the best ee mian in the west

The noodles are thinner than user. Most importantly, the dish is less salty than many stalls and does not give me a weird aftertaste. It's a thriving place to have zi char dinner with friends and family. On a side note, a friend told me i can even ask for less salt in my ee mian

10 June 24’

Ordered coffee toast and eggs set meal, to my surprise; was told they don’t have toasted bread, only eggs & beverages order separately!

Their signs board has “ Not available “ for toast bread.

We were so disappointed about their “ not available “ services,

While the prawn noodles stand out as above average, the remaining stalls offer a rather mediocre experience. Particularly, the roast duck stall serves rice that tends to be excessively dry, which may not suit everyone's taste.
Delicious food by  roast pork stall, vegetarian stall, zhi char stall, chicken rice stall, mixed rice economy rice / porridge

Best coffee in Choa Chu Kang. Frankly speaking most coffee in Singapore can not drink. If at  northern Thailand when I drank the coffee with my friends ,I can drank two or  three cups at once . It is fragrance.Use half  cup of coffee powder and through the drip kettle to make one cup of coffee is the best
